Citation.sAbstract: Densities, ?, viscosities, ?, speeds of sound, u, and refractive indices, n D, of binary liquid mixtures of 1-decanol with o-chlorotoluene, m-chlorotoluene, and p-chlorotoluene have been measured over the entire range of composition at 298.15 K, 303.15 K, and 308.15 K and at atmospheric pressure. From the experimental data of density, speed of sound, viscosity and refractive index, the values of the excess molar volume, V E, deviations in isentropic compressibility, ?? S , and deviations in molar refraction, ?R, have been calculated. The calculated excess and deviation functions have been analyzed in terms of molecular interactions and structural effects.
